wiki.content:
"Dakota" is a song by the Welsh band Stereophonics. It was the first single from their fifth studio album Language. Sex. Violence. Other? and was released on February 28, 2005. 
 
 It was the first Stereophonics single to reach #1 on the UK Singles Chart.
 
 "Dakota" is also the soundtrack of EA Sports game FIFA Manager 06.

track.name: Dakota
comments: Make me feel like the One (1)
@AcousticVersion songs like "Maybe Tomorrow" were a lot more downbeat whereas this has a more feel good vibe.

I'm genuinely surprised 'Dakota' is so popular... Personally I think, it's their weakest song. How can this be? They've got so much more stuff that's a lot better, e.g. 'Superman', 'Maybe Tomorrow' or 'I Miss You Now'.
Reminds me of a perfect day @ PinkPop-Festival last year..lying in the gras and listening to that song. :-) Just makes me feel good.
